$interpreted: Hestia: Puggi! I was looking for you and then I got captured again! Why the heck'd you have to run up on stage for!?
Puggi: It was more like the stage ran to me~
Puggi: I'm the main character, Hesty. The stage is my true calling~!
Hestia: I don't care if—
Hestia: —Hold on, is this the right way back to our cell?
Alliance Soldier: It's a shortcut.
Hestia: Really...?
Hestia: You again!?
Sennosuke: Took you long enough. What, you stop for tea along the way?
Hestia: What do you want, creep!?

Sennosuke: Creep? Well, that hurts my feelings~
This is just business, no need for insults.
Sennosuke: The arbiter owes me a debt and I intend to collect!
Sennosuke: Don't worry, I don't bite.
Alliance Soldier: Be careful with these two, Boss. They escaped once, I bet they'll try to do it again.
Sennosuke: Thanks boys. I'll take it from here.
Hestia: What!? He's even got the Alliance guards working for him!?
Puggi: Hey, you're working for the wrong side! We're the good guys here!!

Sennosuke: Mmm... sweet but not too sweet. 
Alright, let's deal with these two.
Hestia: Hah~ Hey, we work pretty well together!
Sennosuke: Well, that's embarassing! To think I keep such weak company...
Hestia: Yaaagh!!
Sennosuke: It's alright, I like doing things the hard way! You know why?
Puggi: ...W-W-Why??
Sennosuke: Cause it gives me a good reason to bust some heads!
Hestia: No~~!! Stop!!!
Puggi: Somebody help! He's gonna kill us!!
Puggi: Any passing heroes, this would be your time to come save the day!
Sennosuke: Man, you're a noisy little rat aren't ya! I'm gonna have to shut you up.
Sennosuke: Finally, some peace and quiet. Now...
Ace: What's going on over here!?
Jia-Shen: We heard some calls for help!
Sennosuke: Just some folks who let their pets loose. I'm bringing 'em back home.
Jia-Shen: Hold on, that bird...
Jia-Shen: Oh yeah, that's Pang's friend!
Jia-Shen: I'm pretty sure I just cast him a ballot back at the tournament!
Puggi: You have fantastic taste, sir!
Sennosuke: Keep it down or I'll have you for dinner, you stupid bird!
Sennosuke: Ugh... more trouble than they're worth.
Sennosuke: First it's the damn qilin lord.
Sennosuke: Now some turtle thinks it can stick its nose in my business.
Jia-Shen: I... My name is Jia-Shen. Now, I've been appointed as ambassador of the Desert Kingdom by the queen herself.
Jia-Shen: And I ain't gonna let some gangster mess with Pang's friends!
Sennosuke: Stickin' up for your friends, huh?
Sennosuke: You picked a bad day to come outta your shell, ambassador!
Ace: You're the head of the honey badgers, aren't you? Sennosuke?
Sennosuke: What, the Kingdom of the Sun wants to get their hands on my property, too?
Ace: And what if I do?
Ace: I hear you've got a hand in the black market selling Realgar—you might know it as Ruby Sulphur. Is that true?
Sennosuke: You humans all want a say in Alliance business, don't ya? Why don't you go join the tournament, be our next arbiter.
Sennosuke: Then we'll talk.
Ace: Listen, if it's got nothing to do with my Kingdom, then I don't care how you make your money, or who's sacrificing their lives for you...
Ace: —Or maybe I should go ask the Tiger Tribe?
Sennosuke: Seems like you did your homework.
Sennosuke: Alright, what do you want to know?
Ace: I want to know what you're doing with the Realgar. You can make explosives out of it if you know what you're doing.
Ace: ...Are you responsible for those two letters?
Sennosuke: Letters? What two letters?
Ace: ...You don't know?
Sennosuke: Hah! So that's what you're after?
Sennosuke: Interesting, interesting...
Ace: What?
Sennosuke: Listen, making bombs out of rocks seems fun and all, but it doesn't make me money.
Sennosuke: And I'm not interested in things that don't make me money.
Ace: ...I'll take your word for it, for now.
Sennosuke: So if that's all, I'll be on my way.
Sennosuke: Hey, get up! You want to sleep all day you can do it in a coffin!
Sennosuke: We're gettin' outta here!
Sennosuke: You two are far from home, ambassadors. You might want to be careful whose business you go pokin' your noses in.
Sennosuke: Some people might not be as understanding as I am.
Jia-Shen: Uhh...
Sennosuke: Well then, I'll be seeing you.
